<TITLE> Dhaka shops say will open despite strike </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 13 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka Metropolitan Shop Owners Association has said their members will open their outlets on Monday despite the half-day general strike in Dhaka called by the National Committee to Protect Oil, Gas, Mineral Resources, Power and Ports. "There is no way our members can close their shops on Monday; this is the period most people do their Eid shopping and closing would cause chaos," Mohammed Helaluddin, general secretary of the shop owners association, told bdnews24.com. He said the association had not formally made the decision, but the media was being informed that members would likely open their shops during the strike. "We tried our best over the last couple of days to have the strike postponed, but we failed," said Helaluddin. The national committee, tied to left-leaning political parties, has vowed to enforce Monday's half-day strike despite repeated requests from businesses and the government to call off the action. b
